NastiGi's well-crafted songs are bursting with mainstream appeal.  With solid melodies and extremely catchy choruses, they have ‘ear worm’ potential. Blending 90s Americana with their British rock roots, NastiGi’s trademark sound of melodic, powerful, alternative rock has already made them one of the hottest new acts on the London music scene. NastiGi's recent releases (So I Run, Love Your Enemy) have featured on some of Spotify's premier editorial playlists (All New Rock, New Noise, Rock Out, 100% Rock) and hitting over 1.3 Million streams and 600,000 listeners. NastiGi has been at the #1 position for ReverbNation London and Regional Rock Chart, and #1 for the entire United Kingdom  rock chart. 
Returning with a mix of raw energy, noisy guitar riffs, distorted bass and tight grooves, after playing two rock festivals, as well as securing radio plays and the video ‘Take Me As I Am’ is featured on IndieCast TV's, ‘Pottersfield TV’ in USA, UK, Netherlands and South America. Also featured on Lifoti Magazine,‘Metal In Italy’  & ‘Artistic Echoes’ web magazines amongst others , NastiGi returned with “Dude” released 24th October.  Taking influences from Muse, Royal Blood and Skunk Anansie, NastiGi wrote the single for anyone living their life behind a shadow.
Gianluca, the band leader and songwriter, said “Back in 2015, I had been living with the absolute belief that I could never write a whole song by myself.  In 2017, things started taking a different turn for me and I found myself as the one who was responsible for creating new material in my band back then, so I had to find a way.  And, by 2018, I couldn’t believe I actually amassed enough material to release the whole album.  Well, my self-confidence grew stronger each day, so I kept going! Today, it feels natural and so cool!”
NastiGi had three record-deal offers (iCottage Records, Cave music, and PA74music) during last year but still looking for THE right one to come.
Gianluca said “I believe that is only a matter of time until we get picked up by a major music industry label and see our music on the Billboard Hot 100”.

++++. PROFILE NOTES ++++

Once a wannabe, not yet a has been.

It had been over a decade since I put together a song,
and for that matter basically walked away from music altogether.
Losing hope that I would ever have the time to put into music again,
I finally gave away my 3rd music studio.
I ran across SoundCloud around 2013,
and thought I might take what few songs I had recorded, 
and lay them to rest there.
And there they languished.

HOWEVER, around 2017 I went back to SoundCloud
and began listening a little more and a little more,
and actively taking a part in visiting the sites
of so many wonderful musicians and beautiful songs.
Also, more and more often I would discover that these artists
were blossoming everywhere around the world,
and most definitely worthy of high praise and compliments.

Then suddenly, these old dead soundtracks right here
began to have a bit of life breathed back into them.
From the kind words that began to come trickling in,
I thought, maybe, someday I might give this music thing a try again.

The thing that finally pushed me into action
was a particular SoundCloud artist…Sander Heerings,
AKA https://soundcloud.com/wane-of-summer
 

Not only was he encouraging,
but he began faithfully responding to a few questions,
then a barrage of them.

The final result seemed to be that after a couple of months,
the Old Grinder now has a 4th studio and, finally, a new song.
I hope there may be many more to come.

Thank you Sander, and to the multitude that have dropped in
to listen to these old songs, 
and most of all, for perking up my spirits.

***Please see far below for more details of the team.

Capsule Studio offers you services as follows;

■Music Production

Kevin Bucket and Masaya Hijikata can deal for producing music of client's. As the both are skilled and experienced not only as musicians but also as production team, requests for any styles of music production will be accepted. Also, it can be an option to out source some tasks to our partner musicians if some more musicians were needed.

Planning, recording, mixing can be done on one floor with the studio facility.

*Some sample recordings from our recent works are coming soon.

■Rhythm Section Recording

Since Kevin and Masaya are also both professional instrumentalist, Capsule Studio offers you a tight and solid rhythm section tracks for your music.Whether you want a drum beat sample or have a song entirely played acoustically. Requests for one of the team is also more than welcome.

*Some sample recordings from our recent works are coming soon.

■Room Rent

You can also rent Capsule Studio. The rental can be packaged not only with the recording facility but also the drum kit. The rates are set both hourly or daily, depending on your need. Recording devices, equipments,and anything you need for basic tracking are installed in the studio.

*For the list of the equipments, please contact us directly.

■Music Lesson ( Bass, Drums )

Capsule Studio offers also music lessons by the team. Kevin Bucket on Bass Guitar and Masaya Hijikata on drums. Both instructors have their own method on playing each instruments and also much experience in diverse styles of music. From beginner to serious learner, lessons will be prepared as you request.

■ETC...

I have a wide taste in music. But at the same time I'm also quite picky, if I have to say so myself. Most music in my personal playlists is Electronic and Rock, but I also like Rap, Metal, Classical and more. 

Within in Electronic I enjoy things like plain Electro, Techno, House, Chill/Progressive House, Trance, Synthwave/Retro Electro, Tropical House, Deep House, Trap and Dance. I like both Electronic with vocals and without vocals, but I don't like vocals as a selling point of an Electro song. I like a good, catchy beat or a good melody. Things shouldn't be too repetitive for me. I enjoy variation in a song and I appreciate originality. The individual sections of a song must be connected well, or in case of a build-up it must feel natural.

Aside from a few songs I despise Big Room and Dubstep.

Yatzel Elier Calderon Rivera (22 July 2004 ), Known As by his stage name YECR, is a Puerto Rican Rapper. His music is defined as Hip Hop and Reggaeton, but he has incorporated various other genres into his music, including R&B, Bachata, 

Yatzel Elier Calderon Rivera was born on July 22, 2004, in Bayamón, Puerto Rico. In middle school He was Known as YECR for the music he made in the school and all the freestyles he would do. He was shy in high school, he would often create freestyle to entertain his friends and Students in the school, After developing a reputation at his school from his creativity and humor. 


This teenage interests also included Playing Video Games, Running, And Playing Sports and Singing , All of which influenced his Artist sense. Speaking From his distance from the Indieify Distribution .While working as a Distribution at Independent Music in Milford, Delaware Since 2018, YECR released music as an independent artist on SoundCloud, where his song "Liquor ".

Career

In the summer of 201, YECR signed himself A Record Named YECR MUSIC RECORDS. Throughout his career, YECR has frequently collaborated with a Artist Named Yung Hush. YECR gained popularity on SoundCloud and eventually signed himself to a record label. Following the release of his breakthrough single "Bonnie & Clyde" in late 2021,

His collaborative Song with Yung Hush, Bonnie & Clyde, In 2021, YECR began making More songs With Yung Hush.

He was featured in Yung Hush single "No Bank", released in February 2021. Starting in February 2021, YECR Made More Beats , Liquor . Also in Feburary 2021, YECR track, "Liquor " Had Gotten over 15K Streams On SoundCloud. 

Artistry YECR is primarily a Latin trap and Reggaeton artist. YECR sings and raps , As a child, he was loved to dance to salsa and merengue. He became influenced by trap and hip-hop.

 Daddy Yankee is a major influence on YECR but Yandel is his greatest inspiration; he later said that growing up, he would Always Rap to other people who were bullying him. Though primarily a trap and Reggaeton artist, his songs also include influence from EDM, pop, and Rap. 


YECR quirky social media has gained attention during the COVID-19 pandemic. And He has Released his new Single Called (We Going To Space With The Wolves) On SoundCloud On June 4th 2021. Which Is Now Available on all Music Platforms. Up In space was now released and now YECR is working on another music to release in the future ~ Yatzel Elier Calderon Rivera

Alex Haw is and artist/architect & director of atmos.

atmos is an award-winning multidisciplinary  art+architecture+design practice (est. 2007) that works internationally across scales and media - from small-scale product-design to large-scale master-plans, with core expertise in public installations and bespoke residential environments. 

Their work centres on innovative sculptural designs that often incorporate cutting-edge digital fabrication and data mapping. They creat work addressing all the senses, with projects that reward close inspection yet abide in the memory, merging meaning and sensuality.

They have exhibited widely and been widely published on TV (BBC, Channel 4), in national newspapers (Financial Times, Sunday Times, Telegraph, Guardian, Independent, etc.) and international design magazines (Icon, Dezeen, Wallpaper, WIRED, Blueprint etc.). 
Haw graduated with a Fulbright from Princeton and a 1st from the Bartlett.

Alex has taught Design Studios at the Architectural Association, Cambridge University, the Royal College of Art and TU Vienna. He graduated on a Fulbright from Princeton University and with a 1st from the Bartlett, UCL. He writes and lectures widely.

He played the lead psycho in Chris Nolan's 1st feature film, Following.

He runs a weekly social exploration of world food (Latitudinal Cuisine - ). 
& he throws lots of big parties.


He doesn't make any music - but wishes he could.

Passionate in electronic music since many years, the Brice Tens's style was shaped thoughout his musical experiences. Whether it was in France, throughout his trips in Europe, or North America. His many trips to Ibiza, Miami and Las Vegas, as well as his endless nights in London, Paris, Lyon, or Grenoble - participating in various events has greatly influenced his musical personality.

His sets are mainly composed of tech house and house, underground but also with sonority of techno and disco. By combining different characteristics of various genres, Brice Tens manages to create his own personal and innovative style.
He stands out by placing much emphasis on the contrast between underground sounds and more melodic or groovy sounds.




Passionné par la musique électronique depuis de nombreuses années, le style de Brice Tens se précise au fil de ses expériences musicales, en clubs et festivals, que ce soit en France, dans les autres pays européens ou en Amérique du Nord. Ses voyages à Ibiza, Miami et Las Vegas, ainsi que les nuits londoniennes, parisiennes, lyonnaises et grenobloises sont les principales sources de sa personnalité musicale.

Ses sets sont principalement composés de tech house et de house, underground et entrainante, mais aussi de sonorités techno, parfois disco.
Il se démarque en mettant beaucoup l'accent sur le contraste entre les sons underground et les sons plus mélodiques ou groovy.

Hey Music Lovers! Headstash Music is curated by a fiendish music researcher and obsessed archivist, with a strong bias towards new forms of music, hybrid sounds and obscure rarities. Around 15,000 tracks spread over a couple dozen playlists. Unless you listen to a lot of modern music, some of the more traditional sounding playlists like Jazz, Latin, Middle Eastern and Classical might not be what you expect. The main elements that set it apart would be the emergence of electronica, and the fearless cross-pollination of genres that todays artists are breaking ground with. Other playlists include Ambient, Beats, Disco/Funk, Downtempo, Electronica, Folk, Global Bass, Hip Hop, House, Soul/R&B, Rock, Pop, Techno and more. Most playlists are at or near their 500 song limit!  To see all the genres in a super easy to navigate menu have a look at my blog. It has all these playlists, plus hundreds of Youtube videos, articles and music reviews. See link below. I would love to hear any feedback people have about the music I've assembled, or music in general. Happy listening!

The Forever Now is the solo project of Monty de Luna with frequent collaborator Lauren Austin among others. Started in 2011 as “W I N C H E S T E R” from Winchester St. in Toronto, the duo carved out a cinematic indie synth-rock niche with their debut EP “If Time is Not Linear, Why Can’t I Forget the Past”. Now, after relocating to Denmark, Monty is back on his own with Lauren as a frequent collaborator, bringing a new collection of singles titled “Terrible Legacy” that take on a darker and more sinister tone than previous work.

“Incredibly beautiful. It is part cinematic, part cosmic, part operatic, and completely dazzling. The production work is sublime […] Simply spectacular.” - The Revue
